{
  "stem": "4284.1",
  "chunk_idx": 10,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 4.7,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Many, many Jews, of course, had managed to leave Germany, and that simply meant those of us who were left were really the recipients of all the abuse and hatred the Germans had to vent, the leftovers.",
      "word_count": 37
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And we were quite spread out throughout the city.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And so consequently, you had maybe one or two families in the neighborhood.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And hey, it was open game.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "You know, get that Jew, and whatever you can do, you're the big shot for it.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So it was a very, you might say, peculiar awareness of how the world around you was crumbling and was crumbling in on you.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And this was, up to 1939, a very common and, of course, very uniform kind of disposition that, at least, children of my age had to put up with.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Did you ever see your father in this time?",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "He was allowed to come home on weekends.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I believe, if I'm not mistaken, one weekend a month in about four years, three-and-a-half, four years-- one weekend a month, and not on a regular basis, yes.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "They gave you a furlough.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And this was, of course, in 1939 that he finally came home before the war started because the work he was forced to do, it was-- had been completed anticipating the 1939 war with-- with France.",
      "word_count": 36
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "After 1939, when the war had started, it became of course, even more incredible to live in Germany.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And the main reason for that, we now had-- to all the burdens we had to suffer, air raids.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Allied bombing took Cologne as a huge and major target because it had railroad facilities leading into all these now occupied countries.",
      "word_count": 22
    }
  ],
